<HEAD>Authorities Defuse World War II Bomb</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAPLES, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Demolition experts on Saturday defused a
500-pound World War II bomb that forced evacuation of about 3,000
people from a Naples suburb.
   The bomb was discovered Friday afternoon during excavation for a
water line in the suburb of Boscotrecase.
   Demolition experts had trouble defusing the bomb because the
fuse had been damaged when the device was struck by the machine
digging the trench.
   Boscotrecase Mayor Pasquale de Falco, who ordered the
evacuation, said earlier that demolition experts had said they
might need three days to defuse the bomb.
   Authorities used loudspeakers, and military police went door to
door to warn residents to evacuate the area.
