<1ST_LINE>r a AM-RussianRoulette     07-30 0237</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Russian Roulette,0243</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Kidnap Victim Terrorized With Russian Roulette</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HUNTINGTON, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two men and four teen-agers were
arraigned Saturday on charges they kidnapped and beat a man, then
terrorized him with a game of Russian roulette before releasing him.
   The 20-year-old victim allegedly owed one of the attackers
$1,500.
   The suspects, who range in age from 15 to 25, pleaded innocent
to assault charges in the July 23 attack, said Detective Sgt. Jim
Powers of the Suffolk County Police Department. They were arrested
Friday night.
   Additional charges of kidnapping and reckless endangerment were
being reviewed by the Suffolk County district attorney's office,
said Thomas Blomberg, chief of detectives.
   The victim's name was withheld and he was placed in protective
custody because one of the suspects was on parole for attempted
murder of a New York City police officer, said Powers.
   The victim was abducted at gunpoint while walking down a street
in Huntington Station on Long Island. He was driven to the back
yard of an abandoned house, where he was forced to disrobe and
kneel on the ground.
   The attackers pistol-whipped, kicked and beat the man, breaking
his nose and jaw, then ``held a gun to his head and forced him to
endure a game of Russian roulette,'' said Powers.
   No weapon was recovered and police were unsure whether the gun
used in the alleged roulette game was loaded, Officer Thomas
Sorriano said.
</TEXT>
